<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="437" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,583,608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="437">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1858" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1858" box="[602,896,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Kolla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paulula">
<emphasis box="[602,720,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="437">K. paulula</emphasis>
(Walker, 
<number box="[828,887,583,608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="437" value="1858.0">1858</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be easily distinguished from the latter by the following differences: scutellum black basally, orange apically, midline orange (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1231,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1301,1323]" captionTargetBox="[364,1234,205,1270]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[349,1238,193,1280]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Kolla emphysematosa sp. nov. A, B, C, D; Kolla prolongata sp. nov. E, F, G, H; Kolla procerula sp. nov. I, J, K, L.; Kolla petalina sp. nov. M, N, O, P; A, E, I, M dorsal view; B, F, J, N, lateral view; C, G, K, O, head and pronotum; D, H, I, P, fac e." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236247/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="437">
Figs 
<number box="[1221,1231,620,644]" pageId="7" pageNumber="437" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
M, 
<number box="[1277,1288,620,644]" pageId="7" pageNumber="437" value="1.0">1</number>
O), aedeagal shaft with a pair of distinct petal-shaped lobes, and a short protuberance between the two lobes (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1298,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,807,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,796,1933]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Kolla petalina sp. nov. A, pygofer side and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, subgenital plate, ventral view; C, subgenital plate, style and connective, dorsal view; D, pygofer processes, lateral view; E, connective, dorsal view; F, style, dorsal view; G, aedeagus, in caudoventral view; H, aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236251/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="437">
