<number box="[1285,1298,655,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="437" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
G, 
<number box="[1330,1344,655,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="437" value="5.0">5</number>
H).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="437" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,692,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="437">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new specific epithet is derived from the Latin word “petalinus”, indicating the aedeagal shaft with a pair of petal shaped lobes.
</paragraph>
